    "body": "Since this issue is specifically about using Ethers.js providers in truffle-config.js, I think we can close this as won't fix. It's not clear that there's value in supporting this, since the work to instantiate an Ethers provider in config is not any easier or less overhead than just following Truffle's own provider configuration patterns.\r\n\r\nLeaving #5947 in this issue's place, to cover the more useful case of using Ethers.js other abstractions in tests and scripts.",
